# ML Notebooks

A collection of machine learning notebooks covering core concepts, algorithms, and hands-on implementations as I work through the fundamentals of ML.

---

## What's Inside

| Topic                 | Concepts Covered                                       |
| --------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |
| Supervised Learning   | Linear Regression, Logistic Regression, Decision Trees |
| Model Evaluation      | Train/test split, cross-validation, confusion matrix   |
| Feature Engineering   | Normalization, encoding, missing value handling        |
| Unsupervised Learning | K-Means Clustering, PCA                                |
| Neural Networks       | Perceptron, backpropagation basics                     |

> This repo is actively updated as I learn. New notebooks are added regularly.

---

## Tech Stack

* **Python 3**
* **Jupyter Notebook**
* **NumPy, Pandas** — Data manipulation
* **Matplotlib, Seaborn** — Visualization
* **Scikit-learn** — Machine learning algorithms
* **TensorFlow / PyTorch** *(in progress)*

---

## Getting Started

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/StarryStarter/ml-notebooks.git
cd ml-notebooks
```

### 2. Install dependencies

```bash
pip install numpy pandas matplotlib seaborn scikit-learn jupyter
```

### 3. Launch Jupyter

```bash
jupyter notebook
```

